RestAssured documentation

1. Create a Maven project

2. Add the following dependencies to the POM.xml file
rest-assured
testng

Optional to add also:
JsonPath
XmlPath
JSON Schema Validation

API to use
https://reqres.in/



3. Keywords used in BDD

given()-set cookies ,  add authentication , add parameters , set headers info etc...

when()-get, post , put , delete - the actual call

then()- validation status code , extract response , extract headers cookies & response body...



4. Validations:

Status Code

Status Line

Response Body

header


5. Request types:

* Get - used to retrieve data from a server at the specified resource.
* Post - used to send data to the API sever to create or update a resource.
* Put - used to create or update a resource will always produce the same result.
* Patch - used to only apply partial modifications to the resource,  you may only need to send the updated username
* Delete - used to delete the resource at the specified URL.
* Head - almost identical to GET, except without the response body, almost identical to GET, except without the response body.
* Options - used to return data describing what other methods and operations the server supports at the given URL, test for fatal API errors.